  "prompt": "I told her I like her, now what?",
  "response": "Great job on expressing your feelings! Now that you\u2019ve told her you like her, here\u2019s what you can consider doing next:\n\n1. **Give Her Space to Process**  \n   She may need some time to think about how she feels. Don\u2019t pressure her for an immediate response.\n\n2. **Respect Her Reaction**  \n   Whether she feels the same way or not, respect her feelings. If she\u2019s unsure or needs time, be patient.\n\n3. **Ask Open-Ended Questions**  \n   If she seems open to talking, you can ask something like, \u201cHow do you feel about it?\u201d or \u201cWhat are your thoughts?\u201d to encourage her to share.\n\n4. **Be Prepared for Any Outcome**  \n   She might feel the same way, or she might not. Either way, it\u2019s important to handle the situation with grace and understanding.\n\n5. **Continue Being Yourself**  \n   Stay authentic and don\u2019t change how you act around her. If she likes you, it\u2019s for who you are.\n\n6. **Focus on the Relationship, Whatever It Is**  \n   Whether she likes you back or not, you can still maintain a positive connection. If she\u2019s not interested, it\u2019s okay\u2014you\u2019ve been honest, and that\u2019s something to be proud of.\n\n7. **Plan Your Next Steps (If She\u2019s Interested)**  \n   If she shares your feelings, you can talk about what comes next, like going on a date or spending more time together.\n\nRemember, being upfront about your feelings is a brave step, and no matter the outcome, you\u2019ve done something meaningful for yourself. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
